a:260:{i:0;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390947781689203705";}i:1;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEuWlb0F9v5";}i:2;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599243208;}i:3;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:837:"BOOK REVIEW!
.
A lot of people recommended John Gwynne’s MALICE to me. And it was... okay. It’s clearly a freshman effort, with meandering storylines and characters that sort of blend together: the work of someone who read Game of Thrones and thought, Hey, I can do that!
.
The good news is that Gwynne’s second series, beginning with A TIME OF DREAD, is far superior and doesn’t require knowledge of his first series to enjoy. Start there and enjoy.
.
